The paper discusses the use of machine learning for managerial decision making problems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically addresses the trade-off between performance and interpretability, which is a common concern in machine learning and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new approach that combines multiple criteria decision aiding (MCDA) and neural networks, which falls under the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). The paper also uses simulation studies and real-world datasets, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretation of machine learning models in the context of human decision behavior, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
